# $HOME .gitignore — defensive structural enforcement of "never push from home dir".
#
# Remote: officialerictm.github.io.git (PUBLIC GitHub Pages site).
#
# Strategy: default-deny everything, then allow-by-exception for files we
# explicitly intend to track. To track a new file, add a `!<path>` line below
# — do not weaken or remove the `*` line.
#
# Why this exists: $HOME holds dotfiles, credentials, ultraplan teleport
# artifacts, transcript fragments, and assorted operational debris. The site
# remote is public. A single accidental `git add .` could publish any of it.
# The behavioral rule "never push from home" is now backed by a structural one.

# Default: ignore everything.
*

# Allow this file itself so the policy can be tracked and updated.
!.gitignore

# Currently tracked files (as of 2026-05-04). To add more, append `!<path>` lines.
!CLAUDE.md
!README.md
!readme.md
